Tristate Holdings Limited Key Developments

Tristate Holdings Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 05, 2017
Mar 27 17
Tristate Holdings Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 05, 2017, at 10:00 China Standard Time. Location: Room 5A, 5th Floor, 66-72 Lei Muk Road Kwai Chung New Territories Hong Kong Agenda: To receive and consider the audited financial statements and the reports of the directors and auditor for the year ended December 31, 2016; to re-elect Ms. Wang Koo Yik Chun as a non-executive director of the company; to re-elect Mr. Peter TAN as an independent non-executive director of the company; to ratify the aggregate remuneration paid to all the directors of the company for the year ended December 31, 2016 and to authorise the directors of the company to fix their remuneration for the year ending December 31, 2017; to re-appoint KPMG as auditor of the company and to authorise the directors of the company to fix their remuneration; and to consider other matters.


Tristate Holdings Ltd. Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Mar 27 17
Tristate Holdings Ltd. reported consolidated earnings results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported revenues of HKD 2,253,655,000 against HKD 2,515,738,000 a year ago. Loss from operations was HKD 63,202,000 against HKD 14,860,000 a year ago. Loss before tax was HKD 61,927,000 against HKD 9,417,000 a year ago. Loss attributable to equity holders of the company was HKD 84,091,000 or HKD 0.31 diluted per share against HKD 45,669,000 or HKD 0.17 diluted per share a year ago. Cash generated from operations was HKD 68 million against HKD 196 million a year ago. Property, plant and equipment was HKD 30 million against HKD 22 million a year ago. Return on average equity (ROE) was 6.4% against 3.1% a year ago.


Tristate Holdings Limited to Report Fiscal Year 2016 Results on Mar 27, 2017
Mar 15 17
Tristate Holdings Limited announced that they will report fiscal year 2016 results on Mar 27, 2017


